The paper focuses on handwriting recognition and generative models using deep learning techniques, which are commonly studied in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. The use of recurrent neural networks (RNNs) also suggests that the paper may fall under the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves character recognition and generation, which could potentially fall under the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
